---
title: "How to install pythhon and jupyter"
description: |
  Before beginner's guide
author: Byron Chu
date: 2023-01-02
---

###### Install Python
For mac users, start with the "Terminal", input: 
```
brew install python3
```
Then check if python3 is available by using:
```
python3 --version
```
If you see the version info, it means the installation is successfull. So, you can use it by call it out: 
```
python3
```
and exit by typing in exit(). 
You can also install a python package like numpy:
```
pip3 install numpy --user
```

###### 2 Install jupyter
```
pip3 install jupyter
pip2 install notebook
```

Call out jupyter notebook by
```
jupyter notebook
```
The jupyter notebook will be openned in your browser. 

